---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Palletizing — Formic"
  description="Robotic and gantry palletizers for mid-market CPG floors. Stable stacks, fast SKU changeovers, sustained throughput — deployed under Formic Full Service."
  ogTitle="Palletizing — Formic"
  ogDescription="Robotic and gantry palletizers built for sustained throughput, with no CapEx and no integration risk."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/palletizing" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Palletizing
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Palletizing</div>
    <h1>Stable stacks,<br><em>every shift.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Gantry and robotic palletizers built for sustained throughput. Clean changeovers between SKUs, consistent stack quality, no worker fatigue, no injuries — and more capacity than the manual baseline they replace.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Haviland_Products_-_Palletizing_poster.jpg">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Robotic palletizer · production cycle</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why It Matters</div>
      <h2>The hardest job <em>to staff</em>.</h2>
      <p>Palletizing is the job no one wants and the job most lines can't fully cover. Repetitive lifts, end-of-shift fatigue, injury exposure, and a hiring funnel that's running dry. It's the single highest-leverage place to put a robot on a CPG floor.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Eliminates the leading source of lift-related back injuries on the line</li>
        <li>Removes the bottleneck that throttles throughput at end-of-shift</li>
        <li>Frees experienced operators for higher-value tasks upstream</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Scope my line →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Haviland_Products_-_Palletizing.gif" alt="Palletizer running at production speed" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Robotic palletizing · 24/7</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Focus-7603.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="img-cap">Vision-guided EOAT</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — How It Works</div>
      <h2>Vision-guided pick, <em>pattern-aware place</em>.</h2>
      <p>End-of-arm tooling adapts to case, bag, tray, or pail formats. Vision-guided pick verifies orientation; pallet patterns are programmed at deployment and swapped in software, not on the floor.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Mixed-SKU palletizing with on-the-fly pattern selection</li>
        <li>Compatible with all major slip-sheet and pallet stretch-wrap systems</li>
        <li>Up to 1,500 cases/hour sustained throughput on standard configurations</li>
        <li>Cell-level integration with upstream packers and downstream wrappers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Specs</div>
      <h2>Built around <em>your line</em>.</h2>
      <p>Modular, prove-out fast. Layouts scale from a single robotic arm in a 12×12 footprint to a multi-line gantry cell with shuttle infeed.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Robotic arm reach: 1.8 – 3.1 m, with extended-reach options</li>
        <li>Payloads: 25 – 200 kg, EOAT-dependent</li>
        <li>Pallet sizes: 36×36" to 48×48", including custom export sizes</li>
        <li>Stack height: up to 96"</li>
        <li>Safety: light curtains, area scanners, full ANSI/RIA R15.06 compliance</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Get a quote →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Focus-7603.jpg" alt="Palletizing cell on a CPG floor" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Single-cell · multi-SKU</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Haviland_Products_-_Palletizing_poster.jpg">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Multi-SKU sustained throughput</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>End the staffing crisis<br><em>at the end of your line.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
